		<description><![CDATA[Dear Colleagues, The Office of the Vice Chancellor for Research [&#8230;]]]></description>
				<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div class="pf-content"><p>Dear Colleagues,</p>
<p>The Office of the Vice Chancellor for Research is delighted by the campus response to the UIC DPI Seed Funding Program. This funding opportunity, as previously announced, leverages up to $10 million from UIC’s royalty revenue as “seed funds” to align new UIC research activities with the DPI mission and priorities. Information on DPI can be found at <a href="https://dpi.uillinois.edu/">https://dpi.uillinois.edu/.</a></p>
<p>Two cycles of funding were announced in October. Due to a strong response to Cycle 1 and a large volume of letter of intent (LOIs) submitted for Cycle 2, we are extending the deadline for Cycle 2 applications.</p>
<p><strong>DPI Seed Funding Cycle 2 proposals will be due no later than 5:00 pm Central Time on Friday, January 18, 2019.</strong></p>
<p>Please visit the DPI Seed Program page for additional information and FAQs at <a href="http://research.uic.edu/uicdpi">http://research.uic.edu/uicdpi</a>.</p>
<p>Sincerely,</p>
<p>Joanna Groden, Ph.D.<br />
Vice Chancellor for Research</p>
